Araripeleon
differs from all the Myrmeleontoidea already described from the Crato Formation in its dense wing venation with very numerous cross-veins and branches of Rs ( 21 to 23 ), broad area of MP 2 with posterior branch of MP 2 ending in CuA (
Martins-Neto, 2000
;
Martins-Neto et al ., 2007
).
